                    <li>The architecturally beautiful mosque Koutoubia will draw one’s attention, and riding through the palm groves on a camel would complete one’s life.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>5. Cape Town, South Africa—An Eden for Nuanced Nature Lovers</h2>
                <p>Cape Town could be rightly said to stand on the divide of magnificence. Wonderfully, it lies between the towering Table Mountain and the bright-washed splendid waters of the Atlantic. Very few places boast quite such stunning natural beauty.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Panoramic views over the city can be enjoyed from Table Mountain, which is accessible via a cable car. Another scenic coastal excursion is at the Cape of Good Hope. </li>
                    <li>In addition to its beaches, which include pristine private ones, it has vibrant suburbs such as Bo-Kaap and cultural treasures like the District Six Museum. It has a lot to offer for all sorts of outdoor activities—from hiking trails and wine tasting in nearby Stellenbosch—it’s a city that has it all. </li>
                    <li>Go visit Robben Island, where Nelson Mandela was kept under lock and key, or simply chill out on the sun-kissed shores of Camps Bay.</li>
                </ul>

