                    <li>Untouched beauty and extraordinary wildlife experiences make this a favourite for adventure and nature lovers.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>9. Queenstown, New Zealand—Adventure</h2>
                <p>Queenstown is one place that meets the needs of thrill-seekers. This top adventure township lies between towering mountains and sparkling lakes and boasts endless year-round outdoor activities.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Bungee jump from the world-famous Kawarau Bridge, skydive over this perfect scenery, or ski in winter—it’s all here in Queenstown, “the Adventure Capital of the World.” </li>
                    <li>Don’t forget to visit the beautiful Fiordland National Park, with its wonderful fjords and hiking trails. </li>
                    <li>After mounds of adventure, you could take a peaceful boat ride on Lake Wakatipu or pamper yourself with some of the local wines.</li>
                </ul>

